Iranian President: If the lifting of sanctions against Iran, Iranian nuclear negotiations are expected to reach an agreement - Xinhua Xinhua Tehran, Dec. 11 (Xinhua Gao Wencheng Wang Shoubao) Iranian President Leahy said in the Iranian capital Tehran on December 11, if the United States lifted sanctions against Iran, Iran's nuclear issue comprehensive agreement negotiations can reach a "good agreement". According to the Iranian presidential website, Leahy said at a meeting with Iranian envoys in neighboring countries that day that Iran has proved its sincerity in the negotiations by submitting proposals to other relevant parties to the Iranian nuclear deal. If the U.S. side makes up its mind , "the road to an agreement will be clear. The parties involved in the Iran nuclear deal began holding talks in the Austrian capital of Vienna in April this year to discuss the resumption of compliance between the U.S. and Iran. The new round of talks began in Vienna on Nov. 29, were temporarily adjourned on Dec. 3 and resumed on Dec. 9.
